            <div class="clearfix text-formatted field field--name-field-body field--type-text-long field--label-hidden field__item"><p>Our seniors' centres offer vibrant and inclusive gathering places for adults aged 50 and over.&nbsp;The Seniors' Centre membership pass can be used at the four City-operated facilities listed below and gives access to the older adult drop-ins, such as social games, book clubs, discussion groups and music groups.&nbsp;This cost-saving option is available to people aged 50+ and is valid for one year after purchase.&nbsp;</p>
<h3>Fees</h3>
<p>Fees shown do not include HST. Applicable taxes will be added during the payment process.</p>
<ul>
<li>Annual membership: $28.34</li>
<li>Drop-in fee: $2.14 (per visit)</li>
</ul>
<h3>Locations</h3>
<ul>
<li><a href="https://ottawa.ca/en/residents/facilities/churchill-seniors-centre">Churchill Seniors Centre</a>,&nbsp;345 Richmond Road</li>
<li><a href="https://ottawa.ca/en/residents/facilities/heron-seniors-centre">Heron Seniors Centre</a>,&nbsp;programs are available at&nbsp;<a href="https://ottawa.ca/en/recreation-and-parks/facilities/place-listing/carleton-heights-community-centre#section-eef66bb8-d494-4758-a18d-a8c12e2f9d0b">Carleton Heights Community Centre</a>, 1665 Apeldoorn Avenue</li>
<li><a href="https://ottawa.ca/en/residents/facilities/kanata-seniors-centre">Kanata Seniors Centre</a>,&nbsp;2500 Campeau Drive</li>
<li><a href="https://ottawa.ca/en/residents/facilities/nepean-seniors-recreation-centre">Nepean Seniors Recreation Centre</a>,&nbsp;1701 Woodroffe Avenue</li>
</ul>
